postcontent:
Up for sale is one gently used (single owner) HK45C (compact) .45 ACP pistol in approx. 97% condition PLUS one HK factory HK45C threaded tactical barrel (total of two HK barrels which function with this pistol included in this transaction).  This pistol is of recent manufacture (date code of BA) and the accompanying factory threaded barrel was one of the last made before HK began serializing their HK45C threaded barrels (at least that is my understanding) – it has a date code of AI.  The pistol has had approx./ est. 300 rnds through the threaded barrel and approx./ est. 200 rnds through the standard barrel.  There are very slight wear marks visible on the edges of the original sight posts despite it not being a carry weapon (this is pretty typical of these pistols).  The two original mags which will come with the pistol also show very light typical wear.  The pistol comes with all original accessories except for the factory gun lock (so, you get the manual; sticker; test casing/ envelope; extra o-rings, spare backstrap, and key in original platic bag, and second 8 round magazine – all in the original black gun case). The threaded barrel also comes with the original green o-ring plus thread protector. The pistol in the pictures is the actual pistol the successful buyer will receive.

Please note, this pistol is for local sale/ local pickup only (I will not ship).  I am available to meet serious buyers during weekday evening hours and Sat/ Sun daytime or evening hours and am furthermore willing to drive a meaningful distance in and around the Puget Sound to meet serious buyers in a public place.  Buyer must be legally eligible to purchase this pistol and must be willing to complete a WA state pistol disposition/ transfer form along with Seller (this is just a local/ state doc) as part of this pistol sale - NO EXCEPTIONS.  This form can be viewed at the following link:
http://www.dol.wa.gov/forms/652004.pdf

title: For Sale:  Tumble lubed hard cast bullets
postcontent:
Tumble lubed hard cast bullets - I currently have .40cal 180gr Truncated Cone, sized to .401.  

These projectiles are made of a lead/tin/antimony alloy, quenched in water as they are cast to make them harder.  They are then sized, lubed with liquid alox and coated with a fine dusting of mica powder to prevent gumming up your dies and giving an extra layer of lube.  I cast these as a hobby, and will have other calibers available as I find the time and have cooperative weather.  I can also do 9mm 124gr round nose, 148gr .38 wadcutters, and .45 230gr round nose, and I may start doing 158gr flat point projectiles in 38/357 at some point in the near future.

Recently, my hobby has taken a very interesting turn into powder coating of the projectiles.  Powder coating instead of tumble lubing offers several advantages.  Since the powder coat covers the whole bullet (minus the base), there is no chance for the lead of the bullet to contact your barrel.  The only fouling I have seen is from the powder residue.  Another upside is the total lack of any sticky coating, so no more waxy stuff on your fingers, in your dies, in your magazines or your firearm.  Those of you who have used plated bullets will find these to be very similar in how they load and what velocities to expect. 

And of course, they look pretty cool - see attached photos.  I currently have capability to do black and red, with intentions of buying more colors and experimenting with creating my own by mixing colors together.

Price for 500pcs:

.40 180gr TC: $35 Tumble lubed $40 for 500)
